00:16:03,529 --> 00:16:04,723
Gloves are symbolic.

250
00:16:05,898 --> 00:16:09,026
They're to keep us away from
the world during mourning,

251
00:16:09,101 --> 00:16:10,193
or something like that.

252
00:16:10,269 --> 00:16:12,100
I don't even know why they do it.
It's an old custom.

253
00:16:12,171 --> 00:16:13,968
Well, at times like these,

254
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:18,470
old ways are supposed
to help, I guess.

255
00:16:22,581 --> 00:16:23,946
I...

256
00:16:25,184 --> 00:16:26,674
I lost my daughter.

257
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:31,214
Me, too. And my wife.

258
00:16:35,794 --> 00:16:37,489
I could use
a cup of coffee.

259
00:16:37,563 --> 00:16:39,793
There's a coffee shop
around the corner.

260
00:16:43,769 --> 00:16:45,600
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

261
00:16:46,338 --> 00:16:49,068
<i>CLARICE: Zoe walks with Our Mother</i>
<i>Goddess Athena now, Lacy.</i>

262
00:16:49,141 --> 00:16:53,737
She will be cared for and loved
and cherished for all eternity.

263
00:16:56,548 --> 00:16:58,482
It's not very
comforting, is it?

264
00:16:58,550 --> 00:17:01,075
Truth is, it doesn't do
much for me, either.

265
00:17:02,755 --> 00:17:03,881
Zoe's gone.

266
00:17:04,356 --> 00:17:07,154
And all the scriptures,
all the prayers,

267
00:17:07,226 --> 00:17:09,217
all the sacrifices
offered in the temples,

268
00:17:09,294 --> 00:17:12,525
none of these are gonna bring
her back to us. Are they?

269
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:16,094
I am angry.

270
00:17:16,735 --> 00:17:18,669
At the Gods?

271
00:17:20,105 --> 00:17:23,370
At whoever did this.
It's not right.

272
00:17:23,442 --> 00:17:24,670
No, it's not.

273
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:31,012
To be cut down when her life
was full of so much promise.

274
00:17:33,585 --> 00:17:35,177
I should've been
on that train.

275
00:17:35,254 --> 00:17:36,380
No.

276
00:17:36,855 --> 00:17:38,482
I should be with Zoe.

277
00:17:39,525 --> 00:17:40,787
I should be dead.

278
00:17:40,859 --> 00:17:41,985
No.

279
00:17:42,594 --> 00:17:44,323
It wasn't your time.

280
00:17:45,431 --> 00:17:47,729
The Gods weren't ready
to call your spirit.

281
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:49,859
They have another
purpose for you here.

282
00:17:49,935 --> 00:17:51,027
Me?

283
00:17:51,870 --> 00:17:55,567
Zoe was somebody special.
A genius.

284
00:17:57,576 --> 00:17:59,874
The things she could do
with a computer...

285
00:18:01,213 --> 00:18:03,613
She just seemed
gifted that way.

286
00:18:05,651 --> 00:18:09,451
If you knew of any particular
work that Zoe was doing,

287
00:18:09,521 --> 00:18:11,751
any work that
you could find,

288
00:18:12,825 --> 00:18:17,125
then perhaps that would be a way
for you to reconnect with her,

289
00:18:17,296 --> 00:18:20,788
to find comfort in discovering
her in a different way.

290
00:18:22,134 --> 00:18:23,396
Reconnect?

291
00:18:23,535 --> 00:18:24,627
Mmm.

292
00:18:55,767 --> 00:18:56,893
SERGE: <i>Amanda?</i>

293
00:18:59,938 --> 00:19:01,200
Yeah?

294
00:19:04,710 --> 00:19:05,802
Lacy.

295
00:19:05,878 --> 00:19:07,038
Hi, Dr. Graystone.

296
00:19:07,613 --> 00:19:08,671
Are you all right?

297
00:19:08,747 --> 00:19:09,873
Yeah.

298
00:19:10,549 --> 00:19:13,143
I know this is gonna sound
kind of weird, but

299
00:19:14,953 --> 00:19:18,389
I was just wondering if I could
sit in her room for a while.

300
00:19:23,495 --> 00:19:25,861
Allow entry Lacy Rand.

301
00:19:25,931 --> 00:19:27,159
<i>Welcome, Lacy Rand.</i>

302
00:19:28,967 --> 00:19:30,025
Thank you.

303
00:19:31,670 --> 00:19:33,467
Stay as long
as you like.

304
00:20:12,344 --> 00:20:14,869
Listen, I should be going.

305
00:20:17,349 --> 00:20:19,044
Thanks for the coffee.

306
00:20:27,593 --> 00:20:28,890
Are you okay?

307
00:20:31,863 --> 00:20:33,763
(CLEARS THROAT)
Sorry. Yeah.

308
00:20:34,933 --> 00:20:36,366
Sorry.
- No, no.

309
00:20:37,736 --> 00:20:39,931
Hey, listen.
I understand.

310
00:20:41,206 --> 00:20:43,174
In about five seconds,

311
00:20:43,242 --> 00:20:44,869
I'm jumping off
a bridge myself.

312
00:20:51,550 --> 00:20:53,484
I needed this,
you know.

313
00:20:55,754 --> 00:20:59,246
DANIEL: Just to sit
and smoke...

314
00:21:00,225 --> 00:21:02,489
It's the easiest job
I've had all day.

315
00:21:04,329 --> 00:21:05,762
Can I offer you
a ride home?

316
00:21:05,831 --> 00:21:08,322
Uh, no, I live
in the city.

317
00:21:09,635 --> 00:21:11,865
Hey, do you follow
Pyramid at all?

318
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:15,566
I've been known to lay a
few cubits on the Bucks,

319
00:21:15,641 --> 00:21:17,165
much to my misfortune.

320
00:21:17,242 --> 00:21:20,439
Yes, they have had better seasons,
but I've got courtside seats.

321
00:21:20,879 --> 00:21:22,312
Any interest?

322
00:21:23,348 --> 00:21:24,508
Uh...

323
00:21:25,050 --> 00:21:27,484
Listen, I've got
an 11-year-old boy.

324
00:21:27,552 --> 00:21:28,917
Is there any chance
he could join us?

325
00:21:28,987 --> 00:21:30,113
Absolutely.

326
00:21:30,656 --> 00:21:33,022
Listen, this is
my private number.

327
00:21:34,092 --> 00:21:37,459
Why don't you give me a call, and
we'll set up the details, okay?

328
00:21:37,529 --> 00:21:38,791
Thanks.

329
00:21:42,534 --> 00:21:43,796
Sir.

330
00:22:13,899 --> 00:22:15,799
<i>(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

331
00:22:34,953 --> 00:22:36,045
Lacy?

332
00:22:38,790 --> 00:22:40,087
Is that you?

333
00:22:41,493 --> 00:22:42,721
Yeah.

334
00:22:44,363 --> 00:22:46,024
I'm glad you're here.

335
00:22:48,333 --> 00:22:50,597
Something terrible
has happened,

336
00:22:51,136 --> 00:22:52,660
hasn't it?

337
00:22:52,804 --> 00:22:54,567
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

338
00:22:55,340 --> 00:22:56,671
(SCREAMS)

339
00:22:58,076 --> 00:22:59,373
(PANTING)

340
00:23:03,548 --> 00:23:04,947
<i>ZOE: So I'm dead?</i>

341
00:23:08,019 --> 00:23:09,384
She's dead.

342
00:23:12,924 --> 00:23:14,152
Yes.

343
00:23:16,328 --> 00:23:18,387
Where did all this
blood come from?

344
00:23:19,831 --> 00:23:21,890
I don't see any wounds
on your body.

345
00:23:25,203 --> 00:23:26,636
I don't know.

346
00:23:28,173 --> 00:23:29,800
Maybe the bombing.

347
00:23:30,342 --> 00:23:31,468
The bombing?

348
00:23:32,944 --> 00:23:35,139
But you weren't
even there.

349
00:23:36,248 --> 00:23:37,408
You couldn't have
been there.

350
00:23:37,482 --> 00:23:38,710
I know,

351
00:23:39,684 --> 00:23:41,413
but still I felt it.

352
00:23:42,354 --> 00:23:44,788
Zoe was working on
a biofeedback protocol.

353
00:23:44,956 --> 00:23:47,390
She wanted me to feel
what she felt

354
00:23:48,427 --> 00:23:49,792
in real time.

355
00:23:51,029 --> 00:23:54,465
She never got it working exactly,
but something happened.

356
00:23:55,534 --> 00:23:57,331
It's like
I felt her death.

357
00:23:58,570 --> 00:23:59,935
Zoe is dead.

358
00:24:01,239 --> 00:24:02,900
What happens to me?

359
00:24:03,742 --> 00:24:07,405
She had some kind of plan for
you once we got to Gemenon,

360
00:24:08,046 --> 00:24:09,980
but I don't even know
what that was.

361
00:24:12,250 --> 00:24:14,684
We're not going to Gemenon
anymore, are we?

362
00:24:18,657 --> 00:24:20,454
(SNIFFLES) No.

363
00:24:21,993 --> 00:24:23,756
What am I without her?

364
00:24:25,931 --> 00:24:28,126
She's me. I'm her.

365
00:24:28,667 --> 00:24:31,602
I'm all that's left of her.
Help me, Lace.

366
00:24:31,670 --> 00:24:34,264
Make me understand.
What am I supposed to do next?

367
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:37,474
I don't have the answers
you want, okay?

368
00:24:37,542 --> 00:24:41,672
I didn't even know for sure if you
were gonna still be here once Zoe died.

369
00:24:41,847 --> 00:24:43,178
You're scared

370
00:24:43,849 --> 00:24:44,941
of me.

371
00:24:46,885 --> 00:24:48,648
Why?
- I don't know you.

372
00:24:48,720 --> 00:24:49,880
You grew up with me.

373
00:24:49,955 --> 00:24:52,253
I grew up
with Zoe Graystone,

374
00:24:52,324 --> 00:24:54,189
and you're not her, okay?

375
00:24:54,826 --> 00:24:58,694
You're something she created.
You're just a thing.

376
00:24:59,331 --> 00:25:02,095
Zoe promised me I'd see
the real world one day.

377
00:25:04,135 --> 00:25:05,625
(CHUCKLES)
And the crazy thing is,

378
00:25:07,906 --> 00:25:10,238
I already knew what the
real world feels like.

379
00:25:11,343 --> 00:25:12,742
I remember it,

380
00:25:14,212 --> 00:25:16,271
just like I remember
growing up with you.

381
00:25:16,348 --> 00:25:17,406
No.

382
00:25:17,482 --> 00:25:20,610
It's true. I've never
been to your house,

383
00:25:22,153 --> 00:25:24,747
never played
in your room,

384
00:25:24,823 --> 00:25:27,087
never puked
in your bathroom

385
00:25:28,326 --> 00:25:30,851
or put on your make-up,
or tried on your clothes.

386
00:25:33,198 --> 00:25:34,495
I'm not a person.

387
00:25:36,568 --> 00:25:37,728
I know that.

388
00:25:40,272 --> 00:25:41,739
But I feel like one.

389
00:25:51,950 --> 00:25:53,178
(DOOR CLOSES)

390
00:26:01,059 --> 00:26:02,492
It's gonna be okay.

391
00:26:02,761 --> 00:26:04,092
It's gonna be okay.

392
00:26:05,730 --> 00:26:06,788
Somehow.

393
00:26:08,700 --> 00:26:09,689
Somehow.

394
00:26:11,736 --> 00:26:12,828
I promise.

395
00:26:13,405 --> 00:26:14,463
I promise.

396
00:26:25,717 --> 00:26:26,843
Lacy?

397
00:26:26,918 --> 00:26:28,180
Dr. Graystone.

398
00:26:28,353 --> 00:26:30,184
What...
What are you doing?

399
00:26:30,255 --> 00:26:31,347
I...

400
00:26:32,357 --> 00:26:33,847
I...
- What?

401
00:26:34,492 --> 00:26:35,857
I gotta go.

402
00:26:36,962 --> 00:26:38,953
Lacy, why are you here?

403
00:27:05,156 --> 00:27:07,056
How does
the defendant plead?

404
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:10,728
Not guilty,
Your Honor.

405
00:27:13,798 --> 00:27:14,787
(GAVEL POUNDS)

406
00:27:14,966 --> 00:27:16,695
The clerk will set a date
for trial within the month.

407
00:27:16,768 --> 00:27:18,497
Bail will be set
at 10,000 cubits.

408
00:27:18,570 --> 00:27:20,595
Your Honor, the defendant
is a known member

409
00:27:20,672 --> 00:27:22,537
of the Ha'la'tha
crime syndicate.

410
00:27:22,607 --> 00:27:24,871
There is a serious
flight risk to Tauron.

411
00:27:24,943 --> 00:27:27,571
The State strongly recommends
that bail be denied.

412
00:27:27,646 --> 00:27:30,080
I thank the State for its input.
Ruling stands.

413
00:27:30,181 --> 00:27:31,170
(GAVEL POUNDS)

414
00:27:31,282 --> 00:27:34,342
Ten thousand cubits for the
bail and 20,000 for the judge.

415
00:27:35,053 --> 00:27:37,954
The Guatrau is very grateful
for the work you've done for him.

416
00:27:38,023 --> 00:27:41,015
He has pledged to help us find the
<i>nothos</i> that killed Shannon and Tamara.

417
00:27:41,092 --> 00:27:43,754
Tell the Guatrau
I said thanks, but no.

418
00:27:43,828 --> 00:27:45,659
(SPEAKING TAURONESE)

419
00:27:47,432 --> 00:27:48,865
We're on Caprica now.

420
00:27:48,933 --> 00:27:52,232
Caprica. What has this frakking
planet ever done for us?

421
00:27:52,303 --> 00:27:53,429
I've got a deposition
in an hour.

422
00:27:53,505 --> 00:27:55,769
No, no, we cannot
let this pass, Joseph.

423
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:57,398
We need to find them.

424
00:27:57,475 --> 00:27:59,306
Let me grieve
in my own way.

425
00:28:04,115 --> 00:28:05,844
Whatever you say,
my brother.

426
00:28:05,917 --> 00:28:09,216
But I will pray to Mars and all the
Gods for a swift and terrible vengeance

427
00:28:09,287 --> 00:28:12,779
to come to those who have torn your
wife and daughter from this world.

428
00:28:13,591 --> 00:28:15,183
There are no Gods, Sam.

429
00:28:16,795 --> 00:28:18,592
(SPEAKING TAURONESE)

430
00:28:30,742 --> 00:28:32,733
<i>CYRUS: Evaluation</i>
<i>protocol 42.</i>

431
00:28:33,478 --> 00:28:38,711
Independent identification, acquisition,
resolution and execution of conflict.

432
00:28:39,350 --> 00:28:40,681
(SIGHS)

433
00:28:42,320 --> 00:28:45,483
I had a conversation with the
Minister of Defense this morning.

434
00:28:45,890 --> 00:28:48,085
The Prime Minister's
getting a lot of heat.

435
00:28:48,426 --> 00:28:51,759
The media is playing up the fact
that we're five years behind schedule

436
00:28:51,830 --> 00:28:54,196
and half-a-billion
cubits over budget.

437
00:28:54,265 --> 00:28:56,733
He's getting a lot
of pressure to yank

438
00:28:56,801 --> 00:28:58,860
the Cyber Combat Unit
contract from us

439
00:28:58,937 --> 00:29:00,666
and go off-world
with it.

440
00:29:01,206 --> 00:29:03,436
They're talking about
going to Vergis.

441
00:29:18,757 --> 00:29:20,054
(BUZZING)

442
00:29:20,725 --> 00:29:26,095
<i>MAN: Evaluation demonstration,</i>
<i>proceed in three, two, one.</i>

443
00:29:27,332 --> 00:29:28,765
(GUN FIRING)

444
00:29:55,059 --> 00:29:57,118
(GUNS FIRING CONTINUOUSLY)

445
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:17,778
I'll be out
for the rest of the day.

446
00:30:18,416 --> 00:30:19,781
No calls.

447
00:30:22,987 --> 00:30:24,614
(BELL RINGS)

448
00:30:27,859 --> 00:30:29,793
(CHILDREN CHATTERING)

449
00:30:34,265 --> 00:30:36,597
Let's go. They're waiting for us, sweetie.
- Willie.

450
00:30:38,303 --> 00:30:39,668
How was school today?

451
00:30:39,737 --> 00:30:40,795
All right.

452
00:30:41,406 --> 00:30:45,570
I got off of work early and thought
maybe we could walk home together.

453
00:30:46,211 --> 00:30:48,406
All right. Okay.
- Stop off for a shaved ice, huh?

454
00:30:48,479 --> 00:30:49,639
You like that?
- Yeah, sure.

455
00:30:49,714 --> 00:30:50,840
All right.

456
00:30:52,550 --> 00:30:56,919
You know, I met a man who offered to
take us to see the Buccaneers play.

457
00:30:56,988 --> 00:30:58,285
What do you think?

458
00:30:58,356 --> 00:30:59,550
Sure.

459
00:31:00,258 --> 00:31:01,816
I thought you
liked Pyramid.

460
00:31:02,794 --> 00:31:03,954
Sort of.

461
00:31:04,529 --> 00:31:06,019
Courtside seats.

462
00:31:07,699 --> 00:31:09,599
Could Tsattie
come with us, too?

463
00:31:10,501 --> 00:31:14,494
You know, I think I want
to give Grandma a night off.

464
00:31:15,406 --> 00:31:17,033
It's a guys' night out.

465
00:31:18,176 --> 00:31:20,736
We haven't been spending
much time together lately.

466
00:31:21,112 --> 00:31:22,443
Ever.

467
00:31:27,886 --> 00:31:29,877
WILLIAM: Do you think
they still feel pain?

468
00:31:30,588 --> 00:31:31,714
Sorry?

469
00:31:32,190 --> 00:31:35,216
You know, Mom and Tamara,
where they are.

470
00:31:35,293 --> 00:31:36,885
Do you still think
they hurt?

471
00:32:18,403 --> 00:32:19,836
<i>(MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

472
00:32:19,904 --> 00:32:21,531
(CROWD CHEERING)

473
00:32:44,762 --> 00:32:46,320
(BEEPING)

474
00:32:48,933 --> 00:32:50,560
(BEEPING CONTINUES)

475
00:32:54,138 --> 00:32:56,663
DANIEL: What?
<i>- I know you said no calls.</i>

476
00:32:57,108 --> 00:32:59,508
<i>Tomas Vergis is on Caprica.</i>

477
00:32:59,577 --> 00:33:02,045
<i>He's meeting Defense Minister</i>
<i>Chambers today.</i>

478
00:33:02,113 --> 00:33:04,911
<i>Obviously he's making a play</i>
<i>for the U-87 contract.</i>

479
00:33:04,983 --> 00:33:06,473
<i>I hate to say</i>
<i>I told you so.</i>

480
00:33:06,751 --> 00:33:09,549
His company is
years behind us.

481
00:33:09,620 --> 00:33:13,420
<i>Word is, Vergis has developed</i>
<i>a Meta-Cognitive Processor.</i>

482
00:33:14,826 --> 00:33:17,556
(SCOFFS) We've been trying to
crack that technology for a decade.

483
00:33:17,628 --> 00:33:19,823
Suddenly he's got it?
I don't think so.

484
00:33:19,897 --> 00:33:23,560
<i>Vergis is going to tell Chambers
that he has an MCP, that much I know.</i>

485
00:33:23,634 --> 00:33:24,965
<i>If it's true...</i>

486
00:33:25,036 --> 00:33:28,437
<i>I mean, if they really have a viable,
independent artificial brain...</i>

487
00:33:28,506 --> 00:33:29,530
Can't be.

488
00:33:29,607 --> 00:33:30,631
<i>... then the only thing</i>
<i>they need</i>

489
00:33:30,708 --> 00:33:32,767
<i>is a robotic body to put it in.</i>
- I know.

490
00:33:32,844 --> 00:33:35,404
I know. First thing is,
find out if it's true.

491
00:33:35,480 --> 00:33:36,845
Saying you've got
the MCP is one thing.

492
00:33:36,914 --> 00:33:39,212
Actually having it
is another.

493
00:33:39,283 --> 00:33:40,716
See what you can find out.
<i>- Okay.</i>

494
00:33:40,785 --> 00:33:42,047
And, Cyrus...

495
00:33:42,720 --> 00:33:47,316
Did you ever hear of these virtual
nightclubs for kids, teenagers?

496
00:33:47,392 --> 00:33:51,226
You know, they hack the Holobands and
create these places where they can go

497
00:33:52,196 --> 00:33:53,356
and do things.

498
00:33:53,431 --> 00:33:57,800
<i>It's only been an underground phenomenon
for about, oh, five years now.</i>

499
00:33:57,969 --> 00:33:59,095
<i>Why?</i>

500
00:33:59,270 --> 00:34:02,171
(SIGHS) Just keep me
posted on Vergis.

