with the Soldiers of the One?

750
00:50:13,043 --> 00:50:15,238
CLARICE: Ben Stark was
a good and decent boy.

751
00:50:15,312 --> 00:50:20,011
He would never be involved with some kind of a...
Of a terrorist organization.

752
00:50:20,083 --> 00:50:23,018
Lacy, did you know
that Ben was involved?

753
00:50:24,755 --> 00:50:27,553
No, and I don't believe it.

754
00:50:27,624 --> 00:50:28,818
What about Zoe Graystone?

755
00:50:28,892 --> 00:50:29,984
What about her?

756
00:50:30,060 --> 00:50:31,391
Were you aware that
she was a member

757
00:50:31,461 --> 00:50:33,588
of Soldiers of the One,
as well?

758
00:50:48,145 --> 00:50:51,342
She's just gone through an
incredibly traumatic event.

759
00:50:52,315 --> 00:50:53,907
Where does the
Athenian Academy stand

760
00:50:53,984 --> 00:50:55,975
on the question of
monotheism, Sister?

761
00:50:56,053 --> 00:50:58,146
Are we under
investigation now?

762
00:50:58,455 --> 00:50:59,820
Just a question.

763
00:51:00,657 --> 00:51:05,117
The Academy is dedicated to
following the path of the Gods,

764
00:51:05,195 --> 00:51:07,095
the Goddess Athena
being our patroness.

765
00:51:07,164 --> 00:51:09,997
We are, however, open
to all forms of worship,

766
00:51:10,300 --> 00:51:12,461
including belief
in a singular God.

767
00:51:13,003 --> 00:51:14,800
That's very tolerant.

768
00:51:15,238 --> 00:51:18,139
And how many of your students
are practicing monotheists?

769
00:51:18,809 --> 00:51:20,572
You know
I can't answer that.

770
00:51:20,911 --> 00:51:23,004
It doesn't
concern you, Sister,

771
00:51:23,080 --> 00:51:26,072
that kind of absolutist
view of the universe?

772
00:51:26,149 --> 00:51:27,480
Right and wrong
determined solely

773
00:51:27,551 --> 00:51:29,849
by a single all-knowing,
all-powerful being

774
00:51:29,920 --> 00:51:32,218
whose judgment
cannot be questioned,

775
00:51:32,422 --> 00:51:34,822
and in whose name
the most horrendous of acts

776
00:51:34,891 --> 00:51:36,552
can be sanctioned
without appeal?

777
00:51:36,626 --> 00:51:39,288
You seem to know a great
deal about the subject.

778
00:51:39,362 --> 00:51:41,296
Know your enemy,
Sister Clarice.

779
00:51:41,398 --> 00:51:43,730
Love your enemy,
Agent Duram.

780
00:51:44,701 --> 00:51:47,169
That is what we followers
of Athena believe.

781
00:51:49,940 --> 00:51:51,635
I'll be in touch.

782
00:52:14,898 --> 00:52:15,057
(BUZZING)

783
00:52:15,999 --> 00:52:17,523
(CROWD BOOING)

784
00:52:18,502 --> 00:52:20,629
Worthless bunch of losers.

785
00:52:27,477 --> 00:52:30,708
You know, I should've remembered
you own the Buccaneers.

786
00:52:30,780 --> 00:52:33,010
A fantasy
since I was a kid.

787
00:52:33,083 --> 00:52:35,313
Now, William,
what'd you think?

788
00:52:35,385 --> 00:52:37,819
I think Jenkins
tanked the game.

789
00:52:37,888 --> 00:52:41,517
Well, maybe you should come
and tell him yourself. Come on.

790
00:52:42,259 --> 00:52:43,851
Yeah, tell me what,
Dr. Graystone?

791
00:52:43,927 --> 00:52:45,292
This young man
would like to discuss

792
00:52:45,362 --> 00:52:47,762
the finer points of midcourt
defense with you, Rod.

793
00:52:47,831 --> 00:52:50,322
Sure, Daniel, no problem.
What's your name, kid?

794
00:52:50,400 --> 00:52:52,425
Willie Adams.
- Willie, I'm Rod.

795
00:52:52,502 --> 00:52:53,969
I know who you are,
Mr. Jenkins.

796
00:52:54,037 --> 00:52:56,096
So, how do you think
we did tonight?

797
00:52:56,173 --> 00:52:57,299
Not that great.

798
00:52:57,374 --> 00:53:00,343
(LAUGHS) Keep it positive.
You're among champions here, pal.

799
00:53:00,410 --> 00:53:03,607
I'd like to speak with your father if
you don't mind hanging out with the team.

800
00:53:03,680 --> 00:53:05,170
Is that okay?
- Sure.

801
00:53:05,248 --> 00:53:07,716
This is Sean. If you want something,
anything, you just ask him.

802
00:53:07,784 --> 00:53:08,910
Okay.

803
00:53:08,985 --> 00:53:10,816
Now, you behave, Son.
- Okay, Dad.

804
00:53:10,887 --> 00:53:12,650
You know,
that was the first time

805
00:53:12,722 --> 00:53:14,849
I've seen him really light up
since the accident,

806
00:53:14,925 --> 00:53:17,792
so thank you so much
for doing this.

807
00:53:17,861 --> 00:53:20,227
Please, please,
it's easy.

808
00:53:21,264 --> 00:53:22,629
And you?

809
00:53:23,333 --> 00:53:25,062
How are you holding up?

810
00:53:25,535 --> 00:53:27,469
You know us Taurons.

811
00:53:27,537 --> 00:53:30,472
We're nothing
if not a stoic people.

812
00:53:31,141 --> 00:53:32,506
(CHUCKLES)

813
00:53:35,445 --> 00:53:41,042
Do you mind if I ask you a somewhat
strange and personal question?

814
00:53:45,155 --> 00:53:49,353
What would you do if you had the
chance to be with your daughter again?

815
00:53:58,268 --> 00:53:59,599
You don't have to answer that.
I'm sorry.

816
00:53:59,669 --> 00:54:01,136
No, no.

817
00:54:01,204 --> 00:54:02,262
It was
a personal question.

818
00:54:02,339 --> 00:54:04,204
I just hadn't
thought about it.

819
00:54:11,715 --> 00:54:15,344
Most of my family, including my parents,
died in the Tauron civil war,

820
00:54:15,585 --> 00:54:17,712
so my brother and I
came here as orphans.

821
00:54:18,955 --> 00:54:22,391
When we arrived,
they drove us to this orphanage.

822
00:54:23,793 --> 00:54:26,956
I remember this field of
wildflowers on the side of the road.

823
00:54:28,064 --> 00:54:31,966
It might seem strange to a Caprican,
but there are no flowers on Tauron.

824
00:54:33,303 --> 00:54:34,497
Not one.

825
00:54:35,872 --> 00:54:38,807
It was the most beautiful
thing I'd ever seen in my life.

826
00:54:39,943 --> 00:54:41,308
All the colors,

827
00:54:42,779 --> 00:54:45,805
the petals,
the softness, and

828
00:54:47,284 --> 00:54:50,117
I wept openly,

829
00:54:51,688 --> 00:54:53,986
for the first
and last time.

830
00:54:56,326 --> 00:54:58,692
So I guess that's
what I'd tell Tamara,

831
00:54:59,896 --> 00:55:02,626
to find those things in life
that make you cry,

832
00:55:03,933 --> 00:55:05,332
that make you feel.

833
00:55:06,903 --> 00:55:08,996
Because they're what
make you human.

834
00:55:10,674 --> 00:55:12,767
I guess that's what
I'd tell Tamara

835
00:55:13,343 --> 00:55:15,004
if I could.

836
00:55:28,191 --> 00:55:29,419
Wow.

837
00:55:29,726 --> 00:55:32,661
William, I'm guessing you'd
like to see the game room, yes?

838
00:55:33,663 --> 00:55:34,789
Yeah.
- Serge?

839
00:55:34,864 --> 00:55:35,888
Go have fun.
SERGE: <i>Yes, Daniel?</i>

840
00:55:35,965 --> 00:55:37,728
Please escort William
down to the game room.

841
00:55:37,801 --> 00:55:39,132
Show him how to use
the equipment.

842
00:55:39,202 --> 00:55:40,794
<i>Right this way, William.</i>

843
00:55:45,875 --> 00:55:47,809
It's quite a place
you got here.

844
00:55:47,877 --> 00:55:51,210
I still miss tinkering down in
my parents' basement, you know?

845
00:55:51,281 --> 00:55:52,976
This all seems
a bit much.

846
00:56:09,132 --> 00:56:10,827
Ever tried one of these?

847
00:56:11,468 --> 00:56:12,628
Uh...

848
00:56:12,902 --> 00:56:14,699
I'm not much
for that stuff.

849
00:56:16,272 --> 00:56:18,297
Indulge me, please.

850
00:56:19,542 --> 00:56:20,634
Sure.

851
00:56:20,710 --> 00:56:23,042
Just step right in here,

852
00:56:23,113 --> 00:56:24,944
if you would. Right there.

853
00:56:25,882 --> 00:56:27,645
This is what happens
when you buy a Holoband

854
00:56:27,717 --> 00:56:29,184
at any retail store.

855
00:56:29,252 --> 00:56:30,412
I saw it on the news.

856
00:56:30,487 --> 00:56:34,423
Basically, I'm going to scan
your image for your avatar,

857
00:56:34,891 --> 00:56:38,691
which is, in essence, a
virtual copy of you, physically.

858
00:56:38,762 --> 00:56:40,389
Now, just stand still.
- Okay.

859
00:56:40,463 --> 00:56:44,160
You're gonna feel a slight
tingling sensation in your skin,

860
00:56:44,234 --> 00:56:46,668
but I assure you,
it's not harmful.

861
00:56:56,646 --> 00:56:58,136
You can step out now.

862
00:56:59,482 --> 00:57:00,972
There you are.

863
00:57:02,118 --> 00:57:03,142
I've looked better.

864
00:57:03,219 --> 00:57:05,119
If you will
just sit here,

865
00:57:05,188 --> 00:57:07,713
we are ready to go.

866
00:57:08,892 --> 00:57:11,827
Now, just relax,
close your eyes.

867
00:57:12,662 --> 00:57:15,426
Remember, it's going
to seem real,

868
00:57:15,498 --> 00:57:19,264
very real,
but it's all virtual.

869
00:57:21,404 --> 00:57:23,201
Just an illusion.

870
00:57:23,273 --> 00:57:24,399
Okay.

871
00:57:35,518 --> 00:57:37,383
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

872
00:57:37,454 --> 00:57:39,183
It takes getting used to.

873
00:57:44,093 --> 00:57:45,856
Can I talk?

874
00:57:46,663 --> 00:57:49,359
I guess I can.
Where are we?

875
00:57:50,366 --> 00:57:53,392
Inside a very basic
computer program.

876
00:57:53,470 --> 00:57:56,837
I haven't had time to do any
decorating yet. Step over here.

877
00:57:58,808 --> 00:58:00,503
Just tell yourself to walk.

878
00:58:14,424 --> 00:58:16,153
What are you
doing, Daddy?

879
00:58:17,227 --> 00:58:18,558
Working.

880
00:58:20,363 --> 00:58:21,796
Joseph,

881
00:58:22,999 --> 00:58:24,398
this is Zoe,

882
00:58:27,103 --> 00:58:28,434
my daughter.

883
00:58:37,180 --> 00:58:38,545
My Gods.

884
00:58:47,390 --> 00:58:48,482
(GASPS)
Boo.

885
00:58:49,158 --> 00:58:50,250
Frak!

886
00:58:51,027 --> 00:58:52,119
(JOSEPH GRUNTS)

887
00:58:52,195 --> 00:58:53,856
What the hell is this?

888
00:58:53,930 --> 00:58:55,261
What kind of sick, twisted
thing are you doing here?

889
00:58:55,331 --> 00:58:56,593
There's nothing
twisted about it.

890
00:58:56,666 --> 00:58:58,395
And I didn't do it.
Zoe did.

891
00:58:58,468 --> 00:58:59,526
Zoe did?

892
00:58:59,602 --> 00:59:02,867
Turns out she was kind of
a chip off the old block.

893
00:59:02,939 --> 00:59:04,167
That's not her.

894
00:59:04,741 --> 00:59:06,936
Our daughters, they're gone.
- Yes.

895
00:59:07,010 --> 00:59:08,170
You know this.

896
00:59:08,244 --> 00:59:12,010
Yes, but what if
they could come back?

897
00:59:13,049 --> 00:59:14,073
You're insane.

898
00:59:14,150 --> 00:59:15,549
Do you know what
your brain is, Joseph?

899
00:59:15,618 --> 00:59:17,313
It's a database and a
processor, that's all.

900
00:59:17,387 --> 00:59:19,753
Information and
a way to use it.

901
00:59:19,822 --> 00:59:21,050
And what my daughter
figured out was...

902
00:59:21,124 --> 00:59:23,149
Was how to harness
all the information

903
00:59:23,226 --> 00:59:24,989
that made her
who and what she was.

904
00:59:25,061 --> 00:59:26,323
It's genius, really.

905
00:59:26,396 --> 00:59:29,695
She took a search engine and
turned it into a way to cheat death.

906
00:59:29,766 --> 00:59:32,428
No, it's... It's an illusion.
You said so yourself.

907
00:59:32,502 --> 00:59:34,595
Yes. You're right.
You're right. She's a copy.

908
00:59:34,671 --> 00:59:38,266
But she's a perfect copy
in every way.

909
00:59:38,341 --> 00:59:39,672
Still doesn't make her
your daughter.

910
00:59:39,742 --> 00:59:40,800
There's an axiom
in my business,

911
00:59:40,877 --> 00:59:44,108
"A difference that makes no
difference, is no difference."

912
00:59:44,180 --> 00:59:47,172
She looks like Zoe,
she talks like Zoe, she thinks like Zoe,

913
00:59:47,250 --> 00:59:48,774
remembers all the events
of her childhood,

914
00:59:48,851 --> 00:59:52,912
has all the same likes, dislikes,
flaws, strengths, all of it.

915
00:59:53,356 --> 00:59:56,086
Who's to say her soul
wasn't copied, too?

916
00:59:56,159 --> 00:59:57,592
You can't copy a soul.

917
00:59:57,660 --> 00:59:59,025
And you would
know that how?

918
00:59:59,562 --> 01:00:02,030
Hmm? How can you prove
or disprove that idea?

919
01:00:02,098 --> 01:00:04,396
Look, I know
what I know, okay?

920
01:00:04,467 --> 01:00:05,900
And I know you can't
copy a person.

921
01:00:05,969 --> 01:00:07,561
I know that
she's my daughter.

922
01:00:07,637 --> 01:00:09,935
I know that
she is my daughter,

923
01:00:10,340 --> 01:00:13,104
and I know it in the only
place that matters. Here.

924
01:00:13,843 --> 01:00:17,404
The only difference between her and the
Zoe that lived in this house is just that.

925
01:00:17,480 --> 01:00:20,779
She lived in this house
instead of a virtual world.

926
01:00:20,850 --> 01:00:23,216
I want to bring her here.

927
01:00:23,286 --> 01:00:26,983
Joseph, I want her to live
in this world once more.

928
01:00:27,056 --> 01:00:30,184
I want to hold her in my arms,
and I want to kiss her,

929
01:00:30,259 --> 01:00:33,251
and I want her to feel
the sun shine on her face.

930
01:00:35,465 --> 01:00:38,730
I want her to see the flowers
at the side of the road, Joseph.

931
01:00:40,336 --> 01:00:43,396
But for me to be able to transfer
the virtual representation of Zoe

932
01:00:43,473 --> 01:00:46,465
you just saw in there into
a physical body out here,

933
01:00:46,542 --> 01:00:50,103
I need a very special, very
particular piece of equipment.

934
01:00:50,179 --> 01:00:51,476
A physical body... What do you mean?
- Yes.

935
01:00:51,547 --> 01:00:52,775
Like a robot?

936
01:00:52,849 --> 01:00:55,317
"Robot" is a crude name
for what we're talking about.

937
01:00:55,385 --> 01:00:56,477
This is a cybernetic
life-form node.

938
01:00:56,552 --> 01:00:57,814
It's still a machine!

939
01:00:57,887 --> 01:01:00,412
It's artificial skin, eyes, hair, make-up.
- It's cold. It's dead. It's...

940
01:01:00,490 --> 01:01:02,219
Yes, but these are
surface details.

941
01:01:02,291 --> 01:01:04,384
That's what we always tell
our children, isn't it?

942
01:01:04,460 --> 01:01:06,394
What matters
is on the inside.

943
01:01:07,497 --> 01:01:11,263
The device that I need is called
a Meta-Cognitive Processor.

944
01:01:11,334 --> 01:01:15,703
The problem is, there's only
one company that has this device,

945
01:01:15,772 --> 01:01:17,262
and it's not mine.

946
01:01:17,340 --> 01:01:18,432
Okay.

947
01:01:18,808 --> 01:01:21,800
The only one in existence is
owned by the Vergis Corporation.

948
01:01:22,545 --> 01:01:24,740
Ever heard of them?
- Yeah, sure.

949
01:01:28,885 --> 01:01:31,285
I know your connection
to the Ha'la'tha.

950
01:01:31,821 --> 01:01:34,312
I know who
and what you are.

951
01:01:35,391 --> 01:01:37,916
I also know about the
pit in your stomach.

952
01:01:37,994 --> 01:01:39,393
I know about the
sleepless nights.

953
01:01:39,462 --> 01:01:41,054
I know about the
wishing and praying

954
01:01:41,130 --> 01:01:44,327
to whatever Gods will listen that you
could have everything back the way it was.

955
01:01:44,400 --> 01:01:46,766
Well, I can bring
Tamara back.

956
01:01:46,836 --> 01:01:48,326
I can bring her back.
- Get out of my way.

957
01:01:48,404 --> 01:01:49,701
You can see
your daughter again.

958
01:01:49,772 --> 01:01:51,865
Isn't that worth whatever
price you have to pay?

959
01:01:51,941 --> 01:01:54,171
If you leave now,
you'll never know for sure.

960
01:01:54,243 --> 01:01:57,371
You'll always wonder.
You'll walk by her room,

961
01:01:57,447 --> 01:01:59,210
you'll see her pictures
on the wall,

962
01:01:59,282 --> 01:02:02,080
and you'll ask yourself every
day for the rest of your life

963
01:02:02,151 --> 01:02:04,984
whether you had a chance
to bring her back.

964
01:02:07,290 --> 01:02:08,723
Now, if I'm wrong,

965
01:02:08,791 --> 01:02:10,850
have me beat up, have me killed.
I don't care.

966
01:02:10,927 --> 01:02:13,157
But if I'm right...

967
01:02:14,464 --> 01:02:19,424
(SIGHING) If I'm right and you have
a chance to see your daughter again,

968
01:02:21,337 --> 01:02:22,929
possibly even your wife,

969
01:02:28,911 --> 01:02:30,811
isn't it worth trying?

970
01:02:51,634 --> 01:02:52,999
Good morning.

971
01:02:55,371 --> 01:02:56,463
Hey.

972
01:02:59,642 --> 01:03:00,904
Morning.

973
01:03:02,245 --> 01:03:03,644
What's this?

974
01:03:04,347 --> 01:03:05,644
I made you breakfast.

975
01:03:06,282 --> 01:03:07,715
You made breakfast?

976
01:03:08,050 --> 01:03:11,213
Excuse me.
I used to cook for you all the time.

977
01:03:12,421 --> 01:03:15,754
Eggs  la Graystone,
wild-mushroom sausage,

978
01:03:15,825 --> 01:03:20,262
rosemary bread and, of
course, your black tea.

979
01:03:23,266 --> 01:03:24,494
Enjoy.

980
01:03:26,969 --> 01:03:28,095
I miss you.

981
01:03:37,880 --> 01:03:39,575
We can make it
through this.

982
01:03:42,351 --> 01:03:43,477
We can.

983
01:03:45,788 --> 01:03:46,982
Together.

984
01:03:48,491 --> 01:03:49,890
Just the two of us.

985
01:03:52,028 --> 01:03:53,154
Yeah.

986
01:04:03,339 --> 01:04:04,636
Thank you.

987
01:04:07,677 --> 01:04:13,172
Eat, and maybe later on, I'll give you
a chance to lose to me in straight sets.

988
01:04:20,022 --> 01:04:21,614
JOSEPH: I need
a favor, Sam.

989
01:04:22,325 --> 01:04:24,486
I don't even know
if it can be done,

990
01:04:24,694 --> 01:04:26,525
but I need
something stolen.

991
01:04:27,730 --> 01:04:28,788
(CHUCKLING)

992
01:04:28,865 --> 01:04:30,332
Really? You?

993
01:04:33,836 --> 01:04:36,532
I'm listening.
- From the Vergis Corporation.

994
01:04:36,606 --> 01:04:38,005
On Tauron.

995
01:04:40,076 --> 01:04:42,772
Tomas Vergis is a good
friend of the Guatrau's.

996
01:04:43,112 --> 01:04:45,546
I doubt he'd sanction
stealing from a friend.

997
01:04:45,615 --> 01:04:48,049
What if I agreed to deliver
the message he wanted

998
01:04:49,218 --> 01:04:50,879
to Minister Chambers?

999
01:04:51,888 --> 01:04:53,480
Isn't this one of those
big lines of yours

1000
01:04:53,556 --> 01:04:56,218
you're always so worried
about crossing, Joseph?

1001
01:04:57,326 --> 01:04:59,487
Are you sure you really
want to do that?

1002
01:05:05,735 --> 01:05:09,068
You're not actually
threatening me, are you?

1003
01:05:09,138 --> 01:05:11,732
Minister Chambers,
I'm simply delivering a message.

1004
01:05:12,575 --> 01:05:15,601
There's no threat, real or implied,
in anything I've told you.

1005
01:05:15,745 --> 01:05:17,076
(LAUGHING)

1006
01:05:19,382 --> 01:05:23,045
You Taurons, you've got stones,
I'll give you that.

1007
01:05:23,119 --> 01:05:25,246
Are you making
a racial comment, sir?

1008
01:05:25,321 --> 01:05:27,653
No more than
you're making a threat.

1009
01:05:29,659 --> 01:05:31,149
Let's be clear.

1010
01:05:32,495 --> 01:05:34,292
I don't like your boss,

1011
01:05:34,764 --> 01:05:37,892
I don't like your planet
and I don't like your people,

1012
01:05:38,501 --> 01:05:41,834
so you crawl under that rock
where your Guatrau lives,

1013
01:05:42,405 --> 01:05:45,932
and you tell him that not only will
I not be pressured or blackmailed,

1014
01:05:46,008 --> 01:05:50,411
but the government of Caprica is going
to take a very special interest in him,

1015
01:05:50,479 --> 01:05:52,003
his business

1016
01:05:53,482 --> 01:05:55,507
and his low-life lawyers.

1017
01:05:59,588 --> 01:06:01,419
Perhaps you should
sleep on it.

1018
01:06:01,490 --> 01:06:03,981
Deliver the message,
errand boy,

1019
01:06:05,261 --> 01:06:06,888
word for word.

1020
01:06:13,636 --> 01:06:16,196
Goodbye, Minister Chambers.
Have a safe journey.

1021
01:06:17,206 --> 01:06:21,233
I'm not going anyplace,
you frakking dirt-eater.

1022
01:08:13,489 --> 01:08:15,684
(BOTH MOANING)

1023
01:08:20,996 --> 01:08:22,623
(SPEAKING TAURONESE)

1024
01:08:23,165 --> 01:08:24,996
(SCREAMING)

1025
01:08:26,235 --> 01:08:27,634
(GRUNTING)

1026
01:08:35,811 --> 01:08:37,176
(YELLS)
(SCREAMS)

1027
01:08:48,824 --> 01:08:50,086
(GRUNTS)

1028
01:08:53,229 --> 01:08:54,787
(MOANING)

1029
01:09:06,509 --> 01:09:07,806
(DOOR OPENING)

1030
01:09:11,814 --> 01:09:13,304
(DOOR CLOSES)

1031
01:09:38,274 --> 01:09:39,605
Hey there, you.

1032
01:09:40,376 --> 01:09:41,775
Always in the books.

1033
01:09:42,478 --> 01:09:44,002
Missed you
at the club last night.

1034
01:09:45,981 --> 01:09:47,243
Missed you
for two hours.

1035
01:09:47,316 --> 01:09:48,544
Sorry.

1036
01:09:48,617 --> 01:09:51,177
I haven't been much of
a friend lately, have I?

1037
01:09:51,954 --> 01:09:53,751
That's fine.
It doesn't matter.

1038
01:09:57,493 --> 01:09:58,619
Look,

1039
01:09:59,328 --> 01:10:00,659
I found something.

1040
01:10:01,997 --> 01:10:05,091
It changed my life.
I want to share it with you.

1041
01:10:05,568 --> 01:10:06,694
Changed your life?

1042
01:10:06,769 --> 01:10:07,997
Sounds stupid, huh?

1043
01:10:09,071 --> 01:10:11,938
Look, it's not.
It's real.

1044
01:10:13,709 --> 01:10:14,733
Come with us.

1045
01:10:14,810 --> 01:10:15,868
To what?

1046
01:10:16,312 --> 01:10:17,301
A prayer meeting.

1047
01:10:17,379 --> 01:10:18,403
Because I don't go
to enough of those.

1048
01:10:18,480 --> 01:10:19,538
This one is different.

1049
01:10:19,615 --> 01:10:20,946
You pray, Lace,

1050
01:10:22,351 --> 01:10:24,148
but your Gods
don't answer.

1051
01:10:24,486 --> 01:10:26,613
You hurt,
but your Gods don't heal.

1052
01:10:27,656 --> 01:10:29,521
You go to the V-Club
for sex and sin,

1053
01:10:29,592 --> 01:10:32,220
but it doesn't fill
the void in your soul.

1054
01:10:35,898 --> 01:10:38,594
There is truth
in the world, Lace.

1055
01:10:39,635 --> 01:10:41,830
There is a right
and there is a wrong.

1056
01:10:43,505 --> 01:10:45,405
And there is a God,

1057
01:10:46,709 --> 01:10:48,904
a God who knows
the difference.

1058
01:11:00,623 --> 01:11:01,954
<i>LACY: That's</i>
<i>how it started.</i>

1059
01:11:04,793 --> 01:11:06,556
That's how
I got involved.

1060
01:11:09,064 --> 01:11:11,259
I didn't know
what to do, Sister,

1061
01:11:13,068 --> 01:11:14,330
where to go.

1062
01:11:15,904 --> 01:11:19,431
You did the right thing by
coming to see me with this, Lacy.

1063
01:11:21,710 --> 01:11:24,645
I, too, used to feel
a void in my soul.

1064
01:11:27,383 --> 01:11:30,352
I, too, once hungered
to know right from wrong.

1065
01:11:33,989 --> 01:11:35,547
But not anymore.

1066
01:11:50,973 --> 01:11:52,133
Sister?

1067
01:11:53,342 --> 01:11:54,604
You're not alone.

1068
01:12:02,117 --> 01:12:03,379
(CRYING)

1069
01:12:10,326 --> 01:12:12,988
So then, Ben did have something
to do with the bombing.

1070
01:12:14,630 --> 01:12:16,359
He was the terrorist.

1071
01:12:18,500 --> 01:12:22,630
Labels like "terrorist" are what
this corrupt and decadent culture

1072
01:12:22,705 --> 01:12:25,868
calls people who are trying to
fight the real evil in this world.

1073
01:12:26,608 --> 01:12:30,339
Ben was eager to strike against all that
was slowly choking this world to death,

1074
01:12:30,412 --> 01:12:33,347
and so he did
something premature,

1075
01:12:35,050 --> 01:12:37,109
something unauthorized.

1076
01:12:38,754 --> 01:12:42,781
But was blowing up that
train evil, wrong? No.

1077
01:12:44,326 --> 01:12:48,285
He was fighting evil
with all his heart.

1078
01:12:53,102 --> 01:12:54,364
And Zoe?

1079
01:12:57,773 --> 01:13:01,038
You have no idea how
special Zoe was to us.

1080
01:13:03,712 --> 01:13:05,145
Or is.

1081
01:13:18,994 --> 01:13:20,393
DANIEL: Oh!

1082
01:13:21,764 --> 01:13:23,732
I gotta hand it to Vergis,

1083
01:13:25,000 --> 01:13:26,729
it's an elegant design.

1084
01:13:27,302 --> 01:13:28,826
But will it work?

1085
01:13:29,671 --> 01:13:33,937
Well, I won't know until I
put it into a cybernetic body

1086
01:13:34,009 --> 01:13:36,500
and try and download
Zoe's avatar into it.

1087
01:13:36,578 --> 01:13:37,909
How long?

1088
01:13:38,447 --> 01:13:41,143
Well, a couple of days,
at least.

1089
01:13:43,318 --> 01:13:45,252
I do have a surprise
for you, though.

1090
01:13:47,756 --> 01:13:49,621
Your daughter's
avatar is ready.

1091
01:13:49,691 --> 01:13:50,749
What?

1092
01:13:50,826 --> 01:13:52,691
I used Zoe's original
avatar program

1093
01:13:52,761 --> 01:13:55,423
to search and download
any data on Tamara Adams.

1094
01:13:55,497 --> 01:13:58,125
School records,
medical DNA, you name it.

1095
01:13:58,200 --> 01:14:00,168
About 300 megabytes' worth.

1096
01:14:00,235 --> 01:14:03,068
You mean,
she's in there?

1097
01:14:03,138 --> 01:14:04,765
Yeah, the more I work
with Zoe's code,

1098
01:14:04,840 --> 01:14:08,003
the more I realize she was
nothing short of a computer genius.

1099
01:14:08,076 --> 01:14:09,566
I want to see her.

1100
01:14:10,579 --> 01:14:11,841
Thought you might.

1101
01:14:30,032 --> 01:14:31,124
Baby?

1102
01:14:35,337 --> 01:14:36,929
Baby?
- Daddy?

1103
01:14:37,739 --> 01:14:38,831
Tammy?

1104
01:14:42,277 --> 01:14:43,369
My Gods!

1105
01:14:45,848 --> 01:14:47,042
Daddy.

1106
01:14:50,552 --> 01:14:51,883
My Gods.

1107
01:14:51,954 --> 01:14:53,182
(CRYING)

1108
01:14:55,424 --> 01:14:58,450
It's okay, baby.
I'm right here. I'm right here.

1109
01:14:59,361 --> 01:15:03,320
I'm so scared.
What is this place? What's going on?

1110
01:15:04,066 --> 01:15:05,055
It's okay.

1111
01:15:05,133 --> 01:15:06,464
I feel so strange.

1112
01:15:06,969 --> 01:15:08,163
I know,
but you're fine.

1113
01:15:08,237 --> 01:15:09,966
It's not fine.
It's not fine.

1114
01:15:10,038 --> 01:15:12,165
This is wrong.
This is so wrong. No.

1115
01:15:12,241 --> 01:15:15,369
I know, I know, I know.
But the important thing is we're together.

1116
01:15:15,444 --> 01:15:16,536
We can be
a family again.

1117
01:15:16,612 --> 01:15:18,307
I can't remember
how I got here.

1118
01:15:18,380 --> 01:15:20,780
And I can't remember
where I was before now.

1119
01:15:20,849 --> 01:15:22,680
It's confusing. I know.
This is gonna take some time.

1120
01:15:22,751 --> 01:15:24,309
This isn't real.
This doesn't feel real, Dad!

1121
01:15:24,386 --> 01:15:26,718
I don't feel real.
I'm real... This isn't real!

1122
01:15:26,788 --> 01:15:28,688
It's not real.
- Willie misses you! I miss you!

1123
01:15:28,757 --> 01:15:32,420
We can be a family together.
We can be a family again.

1124
01:15:33,729 --> 01:15:35,526
My heart isn't beating.
- I miss you.

1125
01:15:35,597 --> 01:15:37,531
Daddy, my heart
isn't beating.

1126
01:15:37,599 --> 01:15:40,159
Daddy, why isn't
my heart beating?

1127
01:15:40,235 --> 01:15:43,068
Why isn't my heart beating?
Why isn't it...

1128
01:15:44,306 --> 01:15:45,568
(GRUNTS)

1129
01:15:46,909 --> 01:15:48,240
(GASPING)

1130
01:15:50,345 --> 01:15:52,108
My baby.
- I know.

1131
01:15:52,180 --> 01:15:54,148
She couldn't
feel her heart.

1132
01:15:54,216 --> 01:15:56,707
She couldn't feel her heart beat.
- She'll adjust.

1133
01:15:56,785 --> 01:15:59,913
She's probably very confused by
everything. It's only natural.

1134
01:15:59,988 --> 01:16:02,616
No! No, it's not natural.

1135
01:16:02,691 --> 01:16:05,751
No, it's wrong.
It's an abomination.

1136
01:16:05,827 --> 01:16:07,556
Well, define "natural."

1137
01:16:07,629 --> 01:16:09,426
These glasses
help me to see.

1138
01:16:09,498 --> 01:16:12,331
Artificial limbs and organs
help millions to live.

1139
01:16:12,401 --> 01:16:14,460
You'd hardly call
those aids "natural,"

1140
01:16:14,536 --> 01:16:15,696
but I doubt you'd
call them abominations.

1141
01:16:15,771 --> 01:16:18,501
That's not what I mean
and you know it.

1142
01:16:19,274 --> 01:16:22,266
Ah. Uh-huh.

1143
01:16:22,878 --> 01:16:26,814
You mean, only the Gods
have power over death.

1144
01:16:29,217 --> 01:16:32,448
Well, I reject that notion.
I reject that notion!

1145
01:16:32,521 --> 01:16:35,285
And I'm guessing that you
don't put too much stock

1146
01:16:35,357 --> 01:16:36,756
in those ideas, either.

1147
01:16:38,594 --> 01:16:41,688
We have a chance to have
our daughters back.

1148
01:16:41,763 --> 01:16:45,164
And your wife. Think of what that
would mean to your son, Joseph.

1149
01:16:46,535 --> 01:16:50,494
How much would it mean to William
to be held by his mother again?

1150
01:16:52,808 --> 01:16:54,207
You're not right.

1151
01:16:54,977 --> 01:16:56,376
You're out of your
frakking mind.

1152
01:16:56,445 --> 01:16:57,639
Maybe.

1153
01:16:58,380 --> 01:17:01,543
Maybe. I've certainly
been accused of worse.

1154
01:17:18,467 --> 01:17:20,492
<i>ZOE: Do you really</i>
<i>think this download is gonna work?</i>

1155
01:17:21,903 --> 01:17:23,336
This is what I do.

1156
01:17:24,172 --> 01:17:26,970
Yeah. This is
what you do.

1157
01:17:28,110 --> 01:17:29,236
What?

1158
01:17:29,811 --> 01:17:31,472
There's a part of me that

1159
01:17:32,881 --> 01:17:34,576
doesn't want this to work.

1160
01:17:36,318 --> 01:17:37,410
Why?

1161
01:17:38,920 --> 01:17:40,512
I don't want to be
on Caprica.

1162
01:17:40,822 --> 01:17:41,914
(CHUCKLES)

1163
01:17:41,990 --> 01:17:43,150
But it's your home.

1164
01:17:43,225 --> 01:17:44,283
No.

1165
01:17:44,760 --> 01:17:45,920
It's not.

1166
01:17:46,561 --> 01:17:48,153
It's never been my home,

1167
01:17:48,697 --> 01:17:51,393
and it stopped being a home for
the other Zoe a long time ago...

1168
01:17:51,466 --> 01:17:52,990
I don't even know what
that's supposed to mean.

1169
01:17:53,068 --> 01:17:56,629
Why do you think your daughter was on
a lev train instead of being in school?

1170
01:17:56,705 --> 01:17:59,230
Do you think she was
just cutting school?

1171
01:17:59,307 --> 01:18:00,569
Going shopping?

1172
01:18:01,276 --> 01:18:03,710
She was leaving Caprica,

1173
01:18:03,779 --> 01:18:04,837
and she wasn't
coming back.

1174
01:18:04,913 --> 01:18:06,278
You don't know what
she was doing, okay?

1175
01:18:06,348 --> 01:18:07,610
You can't know
because you weren't there.

1176
01:18:07,683 --> 01:18:09,412
I know where
she was going.

1177
01:18:09,484 --> 01:18:11,611
She told me
she had a plan.

1178
01:18:12,354 --> 01:18:13,844
She was going to Gemenon.

1179
01:18:13,922 --> 01:18:16,356
And you know why?
Because she found God.

1180
01:18:16,425 --> 01:18:17,653
The real God.
- Stop it!

1181
01:18:17,726 --> 01:18:19,660
The children of Caprica
are lost, Daddy. Okay?

1182
01:18:19,728 --> 01:18:21,286
We are all lost if we
don't turn to the light.

1183
01:18:21,363 --> 01:18:24,992
Listen to me, okay?
We'll talk about this later.

1184
01:18:25,067 --> 01:18:28,002
When are you going to realize
that later is too late?

1185
01:18:28,336 --> 01:18:30,201
When did you ever listen,

1186
01:18:30,706 --> 01:18:32,367
ever want to listen?

1187
01:18:33,709 --> 01:18:35,438
You and Mom,
you knew it all.

1188
01:18:36,978 --> 01:18:40,539
Your arrogance was
killing your daughter.

1189
01:18:42,217 --> 01:18:44,048
And that's how
you lost her.

1190
01:18:44,853 --> 01:18:46,411
Not to some bomb.

1191
01:20:51,947 --> 01:20:54,108
<i>ELECTRONIC VOICE:</i>
<i>Daddy. Daddy.</i>

1192
01:20:54,382 --> 01:20:55,974
ZOE'S VOICE: Daddy. Daddy.

1193
01:21:13,969 --> 01:21:15,527
(ALARM BEEPING)

1194
01:21:32,554 --> 01:21:33,919
No.

1195
01:21:39,561 --> 01:21:41,358
Oh, no. Oh!

1196
01:21:43,031 --> 01:21:44,055
Oh, no.

1197
01:21:49,137 --> 01:21:50,365
Zoe!

1198
01:21:51,239 --> 01:21:52,536
Zoe!

1199
01:21:52,607 --> 01:21:53,869
(PANTING)

1200
01:21:57,145 --> 01:21:58,407
(CRYING)

1201
01:22:28,076 --> 01:22:29,304
Hi, Dad.

1202
01:22:35,850 --> 01:22:38,444
We're gonna make a new beginning,
starting tonight.

1203
01:22:38,520 --> 01:22:39,919
You and me.

1204
01:22:41,823 --> 01:22:43,347
You know what?

1205
01:22:44,059 --> 01:22:45,822
Our family's gonna
survive this.

1206
01:22:46,962 --> 01:22:48,361
We're gonna get
past this.

1207
01:22:49,931 --> 01:22:52,764
We're gonna put our lives
back together again.

1208
01:22:55,437 --> 01:22:57,132
Mommy and Tamara
are gone.

1209
01:22:59,207 --> 01:23:01,471
They're dead and
they're not coming back.

1210
01:23:02,344 --> 01:23:04,244
So we have to honor them

1211
01:23:05,180 --> 01:23:06,807
by continuing to live

1212
01:23:08,249 --> 01:23:09,716
as best we can.

1213
01:23:13,521 --> 01:23:15,421
I want you to know
who you are.

1214
01:23:15,724 --> 01:23:19,717
We come from a long,
proud line of Tauron peasants

1215
01:23:20,462 --> 01:23:22,987
who knew how to work the
land and still stand proud.

1216
01:23:25,767 --> 01:23:28,634
You're named after your grandfather.
Did I ever tell you that?

1217
01:23:28,703 --> 01:23:29,829
Nope.

1218
01:23:30,672 --> 01:23:31,934
William.

1219
01:23:33,341 --> 01:23:35,673
He was killed during
the Tauron uprising.

1220
01:23:38,646 --> 01:23:40,307
Our last name
isn't Adams.

1221
01:23:42,684 --> 01:23:45,744
I changed it after I
arrived here on Caprica.

1222
01:23:47,022 --> 01:23:48,319
Our family name

1223
01:23:50,458 --> 01:23:51,823
is Adama.

1224
01:23:53,928 --> 01:23:55,156
Adama.

1225
01:23:55,830 --> 01:23:59,322
And it's a good,
honorable Tauron name.

1226
01:24:02,370 --> 01:24:03,632
Come here, Son.

1227
01:24:30,965 --> 01:24:34,731
<i>MAN: Demonstration proceed,</i>
<i>in three, two, one.</i>

1228
01:24:34,803 --> 01:24:36,327
(GUN FIRING)

1229
01:25:31,926 --> 01:25:34,224
<i>ELECTRONIC VOICE:</i>
<i>All targets neutralized.</i>

1230
01:25:37,499 --> 01:25:40,866
<i>Program completed</i>
<i>by your command.</i>

1231
01:25:41,369 --> 01:25:45,738
Dr. Graystone, you've not only
secured a long-term contract

1232
01:25:45,807 --> 01:25:47,707
but you've done a great
service to our planet.

1233
01:25:47,775 --> 01:25:48,969
Thank you, Minister.

1234
01:25:49,511 --> 01:25:52,878
The Vergis Corporation
have made certain accusations.

1235
01:25:52,947 --> 01:25:54,710
If they really thought
they had a case,

1236
01:25:54,782 --> 01:25:56,511
they'd have us
in court by now.

1237
01:25:56,584 --> 01:25:59,348
Yes. But no matter.
It was never our intention

1238
01:25:59,420 --> 01:26:01,479
to take this contract
off-world, anyway.

1239
01:26:01,556 --> 01:26:04,525
It's been my experience
you can never trust a Tauron.

1240
01:26:04,592 --> 01:26:06,685
Deceit is in their DNA.

1241
01:26:09,864 --> 01:26:11,354
What'd you call it?

1242
01:26:11,432 --> 01:26:13,297
Cybernetic life-form node.

1243
